Mr. McCloy.

964
01:35:02.285 --> 01:35:04.829
We have got to conclude our business.

965
01:35:06.748 --> 01:35:07.957
Yes.

966
01:35:08.833 --> 01:35:10.293
Start the transfer.

967
01:35:16.674 --> 01:35:19.510
Follow it and let me know.

968
01:35:46.955 --> 01:35:48.164
<font color="#ff8000">[COMPUTER BEEPING]</font>

969
01:35:49.540 --> 01:35:50.541
<font color="#ff8000">[SIGHS]</font>

970
01:36:02.470 --> 01:36:03.471
<font color="#ff8000">[BIRD COOING]</font>

971
01:36:22.949 --> 01:36:23.992
<font color="#ff8000">[HUGH GRUNTS]</font>

972
01:36:28.871 --> 01:36:31.207
Raise your hands very slowly.

973
01:36:31.874 --> 01:36:33.960
Sure you want me to do this?

974
01:36:34.877 --> 01:36:38.006
Raise your hands very slowly.

975
01:36:54.731 --> 01:36:56.149
<font color="#ff8000">[BOTH GRUNTING]</font>

976
01:37:11.539 --> 01:37:13.249
Ethan. Ethan, do you copy?

977
01:37:19.756 --> 01:37:22.383
Keep it going.

978
01:37:29.557 --> 01:37:33.353
<i><font color="#ffff80">HUGH ON RADIO:</font> Sean,
this rat's reached the end of the maze.</i>

979
01:37:34.437 --> 01:37:35.938
Is he alive?

980
01:37:36.397 --> 01:37:38.775
<i>Yeah, more or less.</i>

981
01:37:40.777 --> 01:37:42.820
Bring him to me.

982
01:37:43.237 --> 01:37:44.280
Go.

983
01:37:51.371 --> 01:37:54.165
Sean, transfer completed.

984
01:38:15.186 --> 01:38:18.189
Well done, Stamp. Well done.

985
01:38:24.487 --> 01:38:25.488
<font color="#ff8000">[GRUNTS]</font>

986
01:38:31.452 --> 01:38:33.413
<font color="#ff8000">[INTENSE GROANING]</font>

987
01:38:37.375 --> 01:38:39.419
Stop mumbling!

988
01:38:39.502 --> 01:38:44.132
I'm afraid he's got no choice.
I believe I broke his jaw.

989
01:38:44.173 --> 01:38:45.174
<font color="#ff8000">[LAUGHING]</font>

990
01:38:45.258 --> 01:38:48.219
Stamp, I'm impressed.

991
01:38:49.387 --> 01:38:50.888
We don't have a lot of time, Hunt.

992
01:38:50.972 --> 01:38:53.766
Whatever you've got to say, say it now.

993
01:38:53.850 --> 01:38:55.101
<font color="#ff8000">[GROANING]</font>

994
01:38:55.518 --> 01:38:58.354
How about giving us a big smile?

995
01:38:58.729 --> 01:39:00.022
<font color="#ff8000">[GROANING]</font>

996
01:39:01.107 --> 01:39:02.108
No?

997
01:39:02.191 --> 01:39:03.609
What are you doing?

998
01:39:05.069 --> 01:39:08.739
Get down on your knees.

999
01:39:11.325 --> 01:39:15.538
Now, this is what's known

1000
01:39:15.830 --> 01:39:18.124
as getting your gun off.

1001
01:40:03.503 --> 01:40:04.879
<font color="#ff8000">[SCREAMING]</font>

1002
01:40:28.903 --> 01:40:30.363
There he is!

1003
01:40:40.998 --> 01:40:42.333
Ethan!

1004
01:40:50.007 --> 01:40:51.259
<font color="#ff8000">[MAN SCREAMING]</font>

1005
01:40:57.974 --> 01:41:00.935
Just back off
and pinpoint their positions!

1006
01:41:59.160 --> 01:42:01.579
Luther, clear the bridge for me.

1007
01:42:05.708 --> 01:42:09.045
Hunt's heading for the bridge,
coming in at 12:00 high.

1008
01:42:25.728 --> 01:42:27.355
Oh, I'm mad now.

1009
01:43:21.409 --> 01:43:22.618
<font color="#ff8000">[TIRES SCREECHING]</font>

1010
01:43:38.134 --> 01:43:41.429
- You all right, mate?
- That punk put a hole in my Versace.

1011
01:43:59.155 --> 01:44:01.657
<font color="#ff8000">[TIRES SCREECHING]</font>

1012
01:44:45.326 --> 01:44:47.620
Ethan, the computer's up. I've got Nyah.

1013
01:44:47.703 --> 01:44:49.330
<i>She's moved out of the city.</i>

1014
01:44:49.371 --> 01:44:51.707
She's on the north bluff
approaching the cliffs,

1015
01:44:51.749 --> 01:44:53.334
<i>but I can't get a visual.</i>

1016
01:44:53.375 --> 01:44:56.545
Copy! She's only got a little time left!

1017
01:44:56.629 --> 01:44:59.256
Track ahead and pick her up!

1018
01:45:06.013 --> 01:45:07.598
I can't get a good shot!

1019
01:45:07.681 --> 01:45:09.517
Ethan, we won't be able to cover you.

1020
01:45:10.476 --> 01:45:14.188
My earpiece is failing.
You've got me on GPS.

1021
01:45:14.230 --> 01:45:16.190
Bring her to me.

1022
01:45:24.615 --> 01:45:27.076
Billy, north head bluff. Haul ass.

1023
01:45:53.978 --> 01:45:57.356
- Get out there and keep firing!
- I can't see anything!

1024
01:45:57.481 --> 01:46:00.109
Slow down, mate, slow down!

1025
01:46:03.863 --> 01:46:04.864
<font color="#ff8000">[TRUCK HORN HONKING]</font>

1026
01:47:38.499 --> 01:47:39.500
<font color="#ff8000">[HORNS HONKING]</font>

1027
01:48:00.437 --> 01:48:02.231
Range is 2 "K."

1028
01:49:23.479 --> 01:49:24.480
<font color="#ff8000">[BOTH GRUNT]</font>

1029
01:49:52.257 --> 01:49:53.258
<font color="#ff8000">[GRUNTING]</font>

1030
01:50:25.040 --> 01:50:26.250
<font color="#ff8000">[YELLING]</font>

1031
01:50:32.464 --> 01:50:34.007
<font color="#ff8000">[BOTH GRUNTING]</font>

1032
01:50:54.236 --> 01:50:55.237
<font color="#ff8000">[GRUNTING]</font>

1033
01:51:14.256 --> 01:51:15.424
<font color="#ff8000">[STRAINING]</font>

1034
01:51:35.986 --> 01:51:38.488
Go ahead. Use it, Hunt.

1035
01:51:39.364 --> 01:51:41.116
It's not a bad way to go.

1036
01:51:42.075 --> 01:51:45.162
It's a lot better than the way
that bitch is gonna die.

1037
01:52:32.793 --> 01:52:34.169
There she is!

1038
01:53:10.539 --> 01:53:11.540
<font color="#ff8000">[GRUNTING]</font>

1039
01:53:36.481 --> 01:53:37.482
<font color="#ff8000">[SCREAMING]</font>

1040
01:54:39.211 --> 01:54:40.420
<font color="#ffff80">AMBROSE:</font> Hunt!

1041
01:54:41.505 --> 01:54:42.506
<font color="#ff8000">[LAUGHING]</font>

1042
01:54:44.132 --> 01:54:47.552
You should've killed me.

1043
01:56:27.235 --> 01:56:29.905
<i><font color="#ffff80">SWANBECK:</font> Miss Hall's blood
has absolutely no elements</i>

1044
01:56:29.946 --> 01:56:31.114
<i>of the Chimera virus,</i>

1045
01:56:31.198 --> 01:56:32.866
<i>not even antibodies.</i>

1046
01:56:34.743 --> 01:56:36.620
Yes, I gathered as much.

1047
01:56:36.703 --> 01:56:42.334
But you were under specific instructions
to retrieve a live sample of the virus.

1048
01:56:42.959 --> 01:56:46.129
I'd be very interested to know how,
after you'd managed this recovery,

1049
01:56:46.213 --> 01:56:48.381
it subsequently got destroyed.

1050
01:56:49.591 --> 01:56:50.842
By fire.

1051
01:56:51.468 --> 01:56:53.762
- It's the best way, really.
- Oh.

1052
01:56:55.430 --> 01:56:59.643
Well, as for Miss Hall,
in light of her efforts

1053
01:57:01.102 --> 01:57:04.231
her criminal record
will certainly be expunged.

1054
01:57:04.272 --> 01:57:05.524
Wiped out.

1055
01:57:05.941 --> 01:57:07.901
I'm assuming you approve.

1056
01:57:11.154 --> 01:57:12.322
I do.

1057
01:57:13.907 --> 01:57:15.700
Where is she now? Any idea?

1058
01:57:17.035 --> 01:57:19.454
I don't know. Not exactly.

1059
01:57:20.830 --> 01:57:23.416
<i><font color="#ffff80">SWANBECK:</font> So what are your plans?
<font color="#ffff80">ETHAN:</font> I don't know.</i>

1060
01:57:24.876 --> 01:57:28.630
<i><font color="#ffff80">ETHAN:</font> Some sort of vacation.
I'll let you know where I'm going.</i>

1061
01:57:29.798 --> 01:57:31.299
<i><font color="#ffff80">SWANBECK:</font> Don't have to do that.</i>

1062
01:57:32.634 --> 01:57:34.553
<i>It wouldn't be a vacation if you did.</i>

1063
01:58:25.353 --> 01:58:27.230
